# Web MIDI Tracker Project

This is a Web MIDI tracker project inspired by Schism Tracker, a free and open-source reimplementation of Impulse Tracker.

## Reference

- **Schism Tracker GitHub**: https://github.com/schismtracker/schismtracker
- Schism Tracker is designed for creating high-quality music using a tracker-style interface

## Project Context

- **Technology**: Web MIDI API, vanilla JavaScript, HTML5
- **Purpose**: Browser-based MIDI tracker with pattern-based sequencing
- **Key Features**:
  - Pattern editor with multiple channels (up to 256 channels like Schism Tracker)
  - QWERTY keyboard note entry (Schism Tracker style)
  - MIDI output to hardware synths and drum machines
  - Pattern order/sequencing
  - Effect commands (volume, panning, portamento, etc.)

## Code Style & Conventions

- Use vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Inline styles in HTML files for simplicity
- Monospace fonts: 'Courier New', 'Consolas'
- Dark theme: black background (#000), dark grays for UI elements
- State management: single state object per tracker instance
- Pattern structure: `{ channels: [[{note, inst, vol, effect, param}, ...], ...] }`
- Default pattern size: 64 rows
- Default channels: 8 (expandable to 256)

## MIDI Implementation

- Use Web MIDI API (`navigator.requestMIDIAccess`)
- MIDI channels: 0-15 (standard MIDI)
- Note format: "C-4", "C#3", etc. (Schism Tracker style)
- Effect commands: hex values (0x00-0xFF)
- Volume: hex values (0x00-0xFF, converted to MIDI velocity)

## Keyboard Shortcuts (Schism Tracker Style)

- QWERTY keys for note entry: Q=C, W=C#, E=D, R=D#, T=E, Y=F, U=F#, I=G, O=G#, P=A, [=A#, ]=B
- Number keys (0-9): Set octave
- Arrow keys: Navigate cells
- Space: Play/Stop
- Tab: Next channel
- Enter: Step down
- Delete/Backspace: Clear cell
- Ctrl+C/V: Copy/Paste

## File Structure

- `tracker*.html`: Main tracker implementations (various versions)
- `midi*.html`: MIDI experiments and synth interfaces
- `midi-synths.js`: MIDI synth abstraction library (BaseSynth, hardware-specific classes)

## Notes

- When implementing tracker features, refer to Schism Tracker behavior for consistency
- Support both manual note entry and QWERTY keyboard entry
- Maintain compatibility with standard MIDI hardware
- Use requestAnimationFrame for smooth playback timing

